Me: I just need to sit down. For a minute.
Me: ...
Me: Strange. The room still feels like they only just stepped out.
Me: I keep their photo in my pocket. The last good day.
Me: But it isn't the good day I keep going back to.
Me: It's the last one. The one I ruined.
Me: If I'd said something different. Anything different.
Me: Maybe they'd have stayed a little longer.
Me: ...Let me go back there. Just for a moment.
